headline: 3 Reasons GIS is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the last six months, General Mills’s shares have sunk to $54.81, producing a disappointing 17.1% loss while the S&P 500 was flat. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
